July 11, 2026 — production-grade hardening audit

Security (Phase 1):
- Added HttpExceptionFilter and AllExceptionsFilter; registered globally in main.ts;
  normalises all error shapes to {statusCode, message, timestamp}, suppresses stack traces
- Enabled explicit CORS via CORS_ORIGIN env var (disabled by default for mobile clients)
- SmsService now wraps raw Axios errors in InternalServerErrorException (was leaking
  internal API URLs and keys in stack traces)
- Completed .env.example with all 9 required vars (was missing NODE_ENV, TEXTBEE_API_URL,
  SMS_API_KEY, DEVICE_ID, JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRES_IN, JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRES_IN, CORS_ORIGIN)
- Deleted auth/constants.ts: dead file exporting hardcoded JWT secret fallback (manually
  delete: Remove-Item src/modules/auth/constants.ts)

Schema (Phase 2, requires migration):
- Added explicit onDelete: Restrict to Booking → customer/worker/category/barangay
- Added onDelete: Cascade to Review → booking and NoShowReport → booking
- Added onDelete: Restrict to Review → worker/customer
- Added @@index([workerId]) to WorkerCategory and WorkerServiceArea
- Run: pnpm prisma migrate dev --name fix-referential-actions-and-indexes

Architecture + consistency (Phases 2-4):
- BookingsModule and AdminModule now explicitly import NotificationsModule
- Added BOOKING_PENDING_EXPIRY_MS, BOOKING_MAX_ADVANCE_MS to bookings.constants.ts
- Added OTP_EXPIRY_MS to auth/otp/otp.constants.ts; replaced inline expressions
- Created src/common/utils/assert.util.ts with assertUserExists, assertBookingExists;
  AdminAssertions now delegates to shared util instead of duplicating Prisma queries
- Merged double-query in BookingsService.findOne() into single findFirst with ownership
  where-clause; contact reveal via destructure-spread at application layer
- Inlined BookingsNotificationService as private notifyBookingParty() on BookingsService;
  removed the extra class per CLAUDE.md fire-and-forget convention
- Added ParseUUIDPipe to all @Param('id') in 5 controllers (bookings, admin, categories,
  workers, reviews) — returns clean 400 before hitting the DB
- Standardised pagination max to 50 (SearchWorkersDto was 100)
- Added @IsNotEmpty() to RefreshTokenDto
- Restricted avatarUrl @IsUrl() to https protocol only

---

July 11, 2026 (code review fixes — second pass)

- Fixed TOCTOU race in admin.service resolveNoShow: assertBookingNotAlreadyStruck was called
  inside the $transaction callback using the non-transactional prisma client; concurrent admin
  requests could both pass the check and insert duplicate strikes. Moved assertion before tx.
- Fixed 404→403 regression in UsersAssertions.assertUserIsActive: missing users now throw
  ForbiddenException (matching old assert.util.ts behaviour), preventing account-existence
  leakage via HTTP status code difference
- Fixed misleading ForbiddenException in ReviewsService.create: null customerProfile was
  coerced to '' and passed to assertCustomerOwnsBooking; added explicit NotFoundException guard
- Fixed hardcoded literal 3 in bookings.service handleWorkerCancellationPenalty: now imports
  and uses STRIKE_SUSPENSION_THRESHOLD so threshold changes apply to both strike paths
- Fixed strikePayload spread order in admin.service strikeWorker: changed
  { issuedBy: user.sub, ...dto } to { ...dto, issuedBy: user.sub } so admin sub always wins
- Fixed assertWorkerIsUnverified double DB fetch in admin.assertions: now composes with
  assertWorkerProfileExists instead of issuing its own findUnique
- Standardised assertBookingExists error message in admin.assertions to 'Booking not found.'
  matching BookingsAssertions; added NotFoundException test for null-profile path in reviews spec
- Test count: 160 → 161

